generated_caption: The line chart illustrates the value of total merchandise exports from Czechia to Russia over a decade, from 2010 to 2019. The trend fluctuates with an increase to $4200 million in 2018 before reaching $4300 million in 2019.

The pie chart illustrates the distribution of counterfeit cosmetics sales in Russia during 2019-2020 by sales channel. The line chart illustrates the annual sales volume of whiting in Spain from 2008 to 2020, measured in thousands of kilograms. The data shows fluctuations over the years, starting with 405 thousand kilograms in 2008 and ending with 37 thousand kilograms in 2020. Sales volumes vary, with peaks at 540 thousand kilograms in 2016 and troughs at 120 thousand kilograms in 2017. Other years display intermediate values, such as 300 thousand kilograms in 2010 and 185 thousand kilograms in 2014.

The bar chart illustrates the prevalence of anxiety symptoms among U.S. adults in 2019, categorized by ethnicity and severity level. It shows four groups: Hispanic, Non-Hispanic white, Non-Hispanic black, and Non-Hispanic Asian. The severity levels are Any severity, Mild, Moderate, and Severe. For Any severity, the percentages are 14.5% for Hispanics, 16.5% for Non-Hispanic whites, 14.7% for Non-Hispanic blacks, and 8.5% for Non-Hispanic Asians. Mild severity has 8.9%, 10.1%, 8.7%, and 5.5% respectively. Moderate severity is at 3.1%, 3.6%, 3.0%, and 1.4%. Lastly, Severe anxiety symptoms occur at 2.7%, 2.8%, 2.9%, and 1.5% for each group.

The bar chart illustrates public opinion on Christmas present choices in Germany in 2020, influenced by the COVID-19 pandemic. It shows three categories of responses: "Disagree," "Neither," and "Agree." The majority agree that they will give away fewer coupons/tickets to cultural events because they have fewer (centers for) them, with 60% agreeing compared to 32% disagreeing. There is also a strong agreement that people expect more toys on Christmas gifts due to spending less on travel and cultural events, with 78% agreeing versus 22% disagreeing. The line chart illustrates the share of domestic and international tourist expenditure in Morocco for the years 2019-2020. In 2019, domestic spending was at 32% with international spending at 68%. The following year, domestic spending increased to 34%, while international spending decreased to 66%. The data points suggest a trend where domestic tourism expenditure rises as international spending declines over the two-year period.

The histogram illustrates the sales value of alcohol-based hand sanitizers in Argentina during the coronavirus outbreak, measured in million Argentine pesos. The data spans three weeks from December 30, 2019, to March 8, 2020. Sales were 6.1 million pesos in the first week, increased to 22.0 million pesos in the second week, and further rose to 27.5 million pesos in the third week.

The histogram illustrates the distribution of online courses published by higher education institutions in Russia on various MOOC platforms as of October 2021. The National Open Education Platform leads with 16 courses, followed by STU.DP with 13 and RosdistantOnline with 8. Other platforms include MOOC.RU (6), Open Online Education (5), People of China (4), Digital University of the Russian Federation (3), Higher School of Economics (3), and the Siberian Regional Center for Competence Development (2).

The line chart illustrates the number of pilgrims on the Way of Saint James by gender from 2017 to 2021. In 2017, there were 153,000 men and 148,000 women pilgrims. The numbers increased each year until 2019, with 165,000 men and 175,000 women. A significant drop occurred in 2020, with 30,000 men and 24,000 women. The trend reversed in 2021, showing 90,000 men and 88,000 women pilgrims.

The bar chart illustrates the popularity of various music genres in Russia for 2020, segmented by gender. Rock is preferred by 35 males and 17 females, while pop songs have a higher female preference with 46 compared to 25 males. Folk songs are equally liked by both genders at 21 each. War and bard songs show a balanced interest between genders, with 21 males and 21 females for war songs, and 19 males and 21 females for bard songs. Jazz has 15 males and 12 females, old romances 11 males and 21 females, and symphonic music 11 males and 14 females. Country, hiking songs, tango, opera, operetta, marches, revolutionary songs, and difficult-to-answer categories all have lower numbers, with the 'Other' category having equal preferences from both genders.

The bar chart illustrates public opinion on various online payment options in France for 2020, categorized by their perceived utility. It shows five features: guarantee of secure payment, possible payment methods, free of charge installment payments, possibility of deferred payment after receiving a product, and one-click payment. Respondents rated these features as 'Very useful', 'Quite useful', 'Not very useful', 'Not useful at all', or 'Don't know'. For example, 65% found the guarantee of secure payment 'Very useful', while 17% considered it 'Not very useful'. The chart reflects diverse opinions across different payment features.

The histogram illustrates the distribution of depression symptom severity among adults in the U.S. for the past two weeks as of 2019. It categorizes the severity into four levels: 'None-minimal' with a value of 82, 'Mild' at 12, 'Moderate' at 4, and 'Severe' at 3.

The bar chart illustrates the prevalence of depression symptoms among U.S. adults in 2019, categorized by ethnicity and severity level. It shows four groups: Hispanic, Non-Hispanic white, Non-Hispanic black, and Non-Hispanic Asian. For any severity, the rates are 17% for Hispanics, 19% for whites, 19% for blacks, and 10% for Asians. Mild cases are 10%, 12%, 12%, and 8%, respectively. Moderate cases decrease to 4%, 4%, 4%, and 2%. Lastly, severe cases are at 3%, 3%, 3%, and 2% for each ethnic group.

The histogram illustrates the number of first prize wins in Spain's El Niño draw across various provinces from 1908 to 2021. Madrid leads with 43 wins, followed by Barcelona with 37. Bilbao has 19 wins, Valencia 15, and Seville 10. San Sebastian, Palma de Mallorca, Zaragoza, Gijón, Santander, and Las Palmas each have fewer wins, ranging from 8 to 5.

The line chart illustrates the value of barley imports in Latin America and the Caribbean from 2016 to 2019, measured in million U.S. dollars. In 2016, the import value was $345 million, which decreased to $262 million in 2017. There was an increase to $300 million in 2018, followed by a rise to $375 million in 2019. The data points for each year are plotted on the chart, showing fluctuations in the value of barley imports over these four years.

The bar chart illustrates Roblox games' global daily active users (DAU) by region from Q4 2018 to Q4 2021. The regions compared are the US & Canada, Europe, Asia-Pacific, and Rest of World. In Q4 '18, DAU was 5 million in the US & Canada, 3.7 million in Europe, 2.1 million in Asia-Pacific, and 2.8 million in the Rest of World. By Q4 '21, these numbers increased to 11.2 million for the US & Canada, 13.5 million for Europe, 11.2 million for Asia-Pacific, and 13.7 million for the Rest of World. Each region shows a consistent upward trend over the years.

The histogram illustrates Hungarian opinions on when elderly people and risk groups will get vaccinated against COVID-19 in 2020, broken down by month. In December, 9% believe vaccination will occur before February, while 17% think it will be some time in spring. January shows an increase with 17% expecting before February and 28% for spring. February sees a slight decrease to 10% before February and 17% for spring. The months of "Some time in spring" and "After spring" have the highest percentages at 29% and 17%, respectively. Lastly, 18% are unsure about the timing.

The pie chart illustrates the distribution of Hungarian enterprises expecting negative COVID-19 effects in 2020 across various sectors. The Accommodation and hospitality sector accounts for 25% of the share, followed by Transportation, warehousing, postal services, and telecommunication at 18%. Trade, repair sector represents 17%, while Other economic and personal services make up 16%. Public administration, education, health, and social care sectors hold 13%, Industrial and mining sector has 12%, Agriculture, hunting, forestry, and fishing account for 11%, and Construction sector comprises 10% of the share.

The histogram illustrates the popularity of various online stores among consumers in the United States as of November 2020. Amazon leads with a value of 58, followed by Walmart at 13, Target at 8, eBay at 7, Etsy at 4, and Kohl's at 3. The data suggests a descending order of preference for these online shopping platforms.

The histogram illustrates Italians' sentiments towards various Christmas 2020 statements. It shows six categories of responses: 'Strongly agree', 'Agree', 'Neither agree nor disagree', 'Disagree', 'Strongly disagree', and 'Don't know'. For instance, 54% strongly agree that this Christmas will be different, while 31% agree. The sentiment is mixed for other statements like 'This Christmas will be sadder' with 28% agreeing and 22% disagreeing. The statement 'This Christmas will be more spiritual' has 12% who strongly agree and 24% who disagree.

The bar chart illustrates public opinion in Argentina regarding abortion legalization in November 2020. It shows three categories of reasons: "Abortion should be legal in any case, because women have the right to decide" with 55% support, "Abortion should be prohibited because life begins at conception" with 39% opposition, and "Other" reasons with 6% support.

The histogram illustrates the timing of gift purchases by Russians in 2020, categorized by time frames before New Year's Day. It shows that 17 individuals planned to buy or order most of their gifts a month ahead, 25 did so two weeks before, 27 bought or ordered them a week in advance, and 29 made their purchases on the few days leading up to New Year's Day.

The bar chart illustrates the year-over-year growth in search queries about electronic education sources in Moscow during March 2020, segmented by portal. Foxford shows a significant increase of 1275 queries, MES has 634 queries, and Uchi.ru reports 148 queries. The data suggests a substantial interest in online educational resources across these platforms.

The line chart illustrates the Gross Domestic Product (GDP) growth in Nigeria from the first quarter of 2019 to the third quarter of 2021, measured at basic prices. The data points show fluctuations over time, with growth rates ranging from -6% in Q2 2020 to 5% in Q2 2021. The chart captures the economic performance of Nigeria during this period, highlighting the changes in GDP growth across different quarters.

The bar chart illustrates Nigeria's main import trading partners as of the 2nd quarter of 2021, with each partner represented by a percentage value. China leads with 30%, followed by India at 8%, and the Netherlands at 8%. The United States accounts for 7%, Russia for 4%, Belgium for 4%, Germany for 3%, Korea for 2%, Brazil for 2%, and France for 2% of Nigeria's imports.

The histogram illustrates public opinion on fashion industry trends in Romania for 2020. Sustainability leads with 53 votes, followed by utilizing social media as a main marketing channel with 47 votes. Genderless fashion and digital outfits receive 42 votes each. New marketing channels are favored by 26 voters, while the absence of seasons in collections and discounts is preferred by 11 individuals. Second-hand fashion garners 11 votes, and genderless catalogs and stores are chosen by 5 people.

The line chart illustrates the timeline of expectations for routine to return to normal after COVID-19 in Italy, 2020. It shows six categories with corresponding values: "Already returned to normal" at 5 and 6, "Jan-Mar 2021" at 4 and 5, "Apr-Jun 2021" at 3 and 4, "Jul-Sep 2021" at 2 and 3, "Oct-Dec 2021" at 1 and 2, and "2022 or beyond" at 0 and 1. The first set of numbers likely represents the number of people expecting their routine to return within each time frame, while the second set might indicate the same but for a different metric or context.

The line chart illustrates the revenue of the automotive industry in Romania from 2015 to 2020, measured in billion euros. The data shows an initial increase from 20 billion euros in 2015 to 23 billion euros in 2017. A slight dip occurs in 2016 at 22 billion euros before rising again to 28 billion euros in 2018 and peaking at 30 billion euros in 2019. There is a noticeable decrease in 2020, with revenues dropping to 25.5 billion euros.

The bar chart illustrates the impact of the coronavirus (COVID-19) outbreak on TV news viewers in Norway during March 2020. It shows the number of viewers for selected television news broadcasts, with NRK1 Søndagsrevyen having 1,060,000 viewers, NRK1 Lørdagsrevyen with 1,040,000 viewers, and TV2 21-nyheter (Sunday) with 530,000 viewers from March 14 to 15, 2020.

The histogram illustrates public opinion on which coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic restrictions should be lifted first in Poland for 2021. It shows four categories: opening hotels and restaurants, with 49 votes; opening shopping malls, with 19 votes; opening cultural and sports institutions like cinemas and theaters, also with 19 votes; and an option to say "I don't know, it's hard to say," which received 12 votes.

The line chart illustrates the value of imported goods into Denmark from 2010 to 2020, measured in billion Danish Krone (DKK). The data shows an upward trend with values increasing from 450 billion DKK in 2010 to a peak of 650 billion DKK in 2019. There is a slight dip in 2016 to 570 billion DKK before rising again to 640 billion DKK in 2018 and then decreasing to 620 billion DKK in 2020.

The histogram illustrates public opinion on the efficiency of the COVID-19 vaccine in Romania for 2020. Respondents were asked to rate their belief in the vaccine's efficiency on a scale from 'to a very large extent' to 'depends on the type of vaccine'. The highest percentage, 29%, believed the vaccine would be efficient to a large extent. A smaller portion, 14%, thought it would be efficient to a very large extent, while 27% considered it to a small extent. Those who believed the vaccine would be inefficient ranged from 25% to 5%, with the smallest group, 1%, stating that the efficiency depends on the vaccine type.

The histogram illustrates public opinion on the priorities of the new Romanian Government in 2021. Education is the most prioritized issue with 43 votes, followed by Health and Economy each with 41 votes. Infrastructure and COVID-19 pandemic response are also significant concerns, receiving 22 and 23 votes respectively. Other issues such as Pension reform, Poverty, Energy, Environment, and the Climate crisis have varying levels of concern, with the least being Industry and Innovation at 1 vote each.

The histogram illustrates the number of employees in various sectors within the European Union (EU27) for 2021, measured in thousands. Public administration, education, and health services also feature prominently with 22,100, 14,200, and 13,200 thousand employees respectively. The line chart illustrates the number of deaths in Texas prisons from various causes, including natural causes, illnesses, and "other" reasons, over a six-year period from 2015 to 2020. In 2015, there were 170 deaths, which slightly decreased to 168 in 2016. The number increased to 213 in 2017 before dropping to 187 in 2018. There was a further decrease to 179 deaths in 2019, followed by a significant rise to 340 deaths in 2020.

The histogram illustrates various reasons why society in Poland in 2020 did not want to be vaccinated against COVID-19. The most common reason was that vaccines were unproven and dangerous, with 43% of respondents citing this concern. Other reasons included vaccine development being too fast (17%), a lack of evidence for efficacy (15%), concerns about side effects (14%), and skepticism due to past vaccine failures (14%). The line chart illustrates the import volume of liquefied natural gas (LNG) into India over nine financial years, from 2012 to 2020. The histogram illustrates biotechnology investment in Spain in 2019, categorized by the origin of funds. Public Administration funds contributed 780 million euros, while investments from own funds amounted to 745 million euros. The smallest contribution came from universities with 5 million euros.

The histogram illustrates public satisfaction with the UK government's COVID-19 response in 2020 across various categories. It shows the percentage of people who are very satisfied, fairly satisfied, neither satisfied nor dissatisfied, fairly dissatisfied, very dissatisfied, and those who don't know. The data includes responses from different demographic groups: 23% of young adults, 22% of middle-aged individuals, 27% of older adults, 24% of students, 25% of professionals, 26% of unemployed, 22% of retired individuals, 21% of parents, 20% of single individuals, 23% of couples, 24% of grandparents, 22% of children, and 21% of teenagers.

The bar chart illustrates the impact of the coronavirus on entertainment TV show viewers in Norway during March 2020, with data segmented by week. It shows the number of viewers for four different TV shows: 'Nytt på nytt' (Friday), 'Alle mot 1' (Saturday), 'Kompani Lauritzen' (Saturday), and 'Farmen kjendis' (Sunday). Similar trends are observed for the other shows, indicating an overall increase in viewership over the period.

The line chart illustrates the per capita consumption of bottled water in the United States from 1999 to 2020, measured in gallons. Starting at 16.3 gallons in 1999, the consumption increased steadily each year, reaching 45.2 gallons by 2020. The data points show fluctuations over the years, with a peak at 28.9 gallons in 2007 and a dip to 27.1 gallons in 2009. Overall, there is a clear upward trend in bottled water consumption over the two-decade period.

The line chart illustrates the per capita consumption of flavored milk and drinks in the United States from 2000 to 2019, measured in pounds. The data shows fluctuations over the years, starting at 13 pounds in 2000, peaking at 15 pounds in 2006, and then varying between 13.5 and 15 pounds across subsequent years. Consumption dipped to 13.5 pounds in 2014 before rising to 14.3 pounds in 2018.

The histogram illustrates the number of commercial nuclear power reactors in the United States in 2020, categorized by years of operation. There are 1 reactor operating for 1-19 years, 2 reactors for 20-29 years, 45 reactors for 30-39 years, 44 reactors for 40-49 years, and 4 reactors that have been operational for 50 years or more.

The bar chart illustrates the market share of different smartphone operating systems across six countries in 2013. The data includes percentages for Android, Apple, Windows, BlackBerry, Symbian, and Other categories. In the UK, Android leads with 75%, followed by Apple at 28%. France shows a similar trend but with slightly higher Android usage (80%). Germany has a more even distribution among the operating systems, while Italy has a significant preference for Android at 65%. The USA is dominated by Android at 51% and Apple at 41%. Spain also favors Android at 72%, with Apple close behind at 30%.

The histogram illustrates the global cumulative installed capacity of wind power in 2019, measured in megawatts (MW), by country. China leads with 245,000 MW, followed by the United States at 106,000 MW and Germany at 63,000 MW. India has an installed capacity of 37,000 MW, while Spain stands at 25,000 MW. The United Kingdom, France, Brazil, Canada, and the rest of the world have capacities of 23,000 MW, 18,000 MW, 16,000 MW, 14,000 MW, and 12,000 MW respectively.

The line chart illustrates the national TV advertising spending during the NCAA Men's Basketball Championship (March Madness) from 2015 to 2019, measured in million U.S. dollars. In 2015, the spending was $850 million, which increased to $870 million in 2016 and $900 million in 2017. The highest spending of $940 million occurred in 2018, followed by a slight decrease to $910 million in 2019.

The histogram illustrates the distribution of leading Windows malware types in 2019. Trojans (general) lead with a value of 65, followed by viruses at 15, and worms at 8. Backdoors have a value of 5, while others are represented with a value of 1. Password Trojans and Crypto miners have values of 3 and 2 respectively.

The line chart illustrates the quarterly subscriber churn rate of Spotify worldwide from the 2nd quarter of 2018 to the 4th quarter of 2019, measured in millions. In Q2 2018, the churn rate was at 5.8 million, which decreased to 5.6 million in Q3 and further to 5.2 million in Q4 2018. The trend continued downward into 2019, with the churn rate dropping to 4.8 million by Q4 2019.

The bar chart illustrates the global penetration of Facebook as of March 2021, segmented by region. North America leads with 71% usage, followed by Latin America/Caribbean at 69%, and Oceania/Australia at 56%. Europe shows a 62% usage rate, while the Middle East has 55%. The worldwide average stands at 35%, Asia at 26%, and Africa at 19%.

The histogram illustrates the highest auction prices of contemporary artworks worldwide between July 2018 and June 2019, measured in million U.S. dollars. Jeff Koons' artwork sold for $93.5 million, Jean-Michel Basquiat's for $26.4 million, and James Rosenquist's for $21.7 million. Other artists featured include David Hockney, Douglas Coupland, KAWS, Christopher Wool, Tracey Emin, Jenny Saville, Pae White, Anish Kapoor, and Ron Mueck, with their respective highest auction prices ranging from $12.7 million to $9.1 million.

The candlestick chart illustrates changes in the Consumer Confidence Index (CCI) in Poland from January 2020 to February 2022, with data points for each month. The chart shows opening and closing prices, as well as monthly high and low prices. In January 2020, the CCI opened at 100 and closed at 95, with a high of 105 and a low of 85. By February 2022, the CCI opened at 75 and closed at 65, with a high of 80 and a low of 55. The data reflects fluctuations over the two-year period, with the lowest point occurring in March 2020 at an opening price of 35 and a closing price of 30.

The histogram illustrates the leading social networks in the U.S. during October 2018, based on monthly active users (in millions). Facebook leads with 207 million users, followed by Instagram at 159 million. Facebook Messenger has 140 million users, while Twitter accounts for 115 million. Google Hangouts and Pinterest have 93 and 80 million users respectively. Blogger, Reddit, Snapchat, and Tumblr follow with 68, 59, 51, and 32 million users, respectively.

The histogram illustrates the number of child abuse victims who saw court action taken in the United States by state in 2019. California leads with 27,000 cases, followed by Illinois and Texas at 12,000 and 7,500 respectively. Other states like Massachusetts, Michigan, and Ohio have figures ranging from 5,000 to 3,000 cases. The data shows a descending trend in the number of cases as one moves down the list, with states such as Vermont, New Hampshire, and Alaska having fewer than 1,000 cases each. The least number of cases is reported by Wyoming, South Dakota, North Dakota, Rhode Island, and Delaware, with numbers below 500.

The histogram illustrates children's media consumption preferences during summer in the U.S. in 2015, categorized by activity and response to increased or decreased usage. For television, 24% preferred much more, while 11% preferred somewhat less. Video games saw 24% preferring much more and 5% preferring somewhat less. Internet use had 22% preferring much more and 10% preferring somewhat less. Movies were preferred with 21% much more and 8% somewhat less. Smartphone usage had 19% much more and 4% somewhat less. Social media had the highest 'not applicable' responses at 28%.

The line chart illustrates the growth in the number of internet users in Brazil from 2017 to projected figures for 2026. In 2017, there were 120 million internet users. The trend shows an increase each year, with 140 million in 2018, 150 million in 2019, and so on, reaching 190 million by 2026. The data suggests a consistent upward trajectory in internet usage over the decade.

The bar chart illustrates the percentage of prison inmates who were abused as children in 1999, categorized by type of abuse and gender. It shows that 18.7% of the total population had been abused before admission, with males at 14.3% and females at 37.2%. For physical abuse, 15.3% of the total were affected, with males at 11.9% and females at 25.4%. Sexually abused individuals accounted for 7.9% of the total, with males at 5.0% and females at 25.4%.

The histogram illustrates the selection criteria for smartphone purchase in China during 2012. It shows that 'Price' was the most significant factor, chosen by 70% of respondents, followed closely by 'Operating system' at 65%. 'Brand' preference came next with 43%, while 'Physical appearance' was valued by 34% of users. 'Pixel' count and 'Screen' quality were considered by 25% and 20% respectively. 'Power consumption' and 'Playing sound quality' were less influential, chosen by 18% and 17% of consumers. Lastly, 'Others' comprised the remaining 22% of selection criteria.

The bar chart illustrates the growth in the number of active internet-enabled smartphones in India from 2011 to 2016, measured in millions. In 2011, there were 10 million such devices, which increased to 25 million by 2012. The trend continued upward with 60 million in 2013, 105 million in 2014, and reached 170 million in 2015. By 2016, the number further rose to 270 million active internet-enabled smartphones.

The histogram illustrates the number of intercountry adoptions involving the United States in 2018, categorized by visa type. There were 2675 adoptions under the IH-3 category, 1100 under IR-3, and 180 each for both IR-4 and IH-4 categories.

The histogram illustrates the cumulative total of Tumblr blogs from May 2011 to April 2020, measured in millions. Each bar represents a month's worth of data, starting with 20 million in May 2011 and ending with 500 million in April 2020. The increments appear consistent, suggesting a steady growth in the number of Tumblr blogs over the nine-year period.

The line chart illustrates the sales share of various retail channels in the U.S. sunglasses market from 2010 to 2011. Independents' share decreased from 4% to 3%, while chains maintained a consistent 6%. Grocery/drug/wholesale club/mass stores saw an increase from 18% to 19%. Sunglass specialty stores grew from 37% to 38%, and better department and specialty stores rose from 10% to 12%. The 'Other' category experienced a decline from 24% to 20%.

The histogram illustrates the number of days it took for COVID-19 deaths to double in select countries worldwide as of December 13, 2020. The data includes various countries with varying doubling times ranging from 14 days (United States) to 297 days (India). Other countries listed show doubling times between these extremes, such as 25 days for the United Kingdom and 186 days for Brazil. The chart provides a visual representation of the progression of the pandemic's impact on mortality rates across different nations within this timeframe.

The line chart illustrates Marriott International, Inc.'s net income worldwide from 2007 to 2020, measured in million U.S. dollars. The data shows fluctuations over the years, with an initial increase from $718 million in 2007 to a peak of $1916 million in 2018. However, there is a significant dip in 2009 to $134 million and another decline in 2020 to $152 million. The net income generally fluctuates between these extremes, with notable increases in 2015 ($862 million) and 2016 ($789 million).

The bar chart illustrates the weekly mobile e-mail access rate in selected countries as of 2016. The data shows that Sweden leads with an 85% access rate, followed by Italy at 83%, and the United States at 84%. Japan's rate is slightly lower at 82%, while the UK stands at 81%. Australia has an 80% access rate, France at 79%, and Germany has the lowest among these countries with a 78% rate.

The histogram illustrates the average monthly user engagement in hours for selected mobile social apps in the U.S. as of February 2022. TikTok leads with an average engagement of 25.9 hours, followed by YouTube at 22.4 hours. Facebook has an average engagement of 16.2 hours, Instagram at 7.8 hours, and Facebook Messenger at 3.2 hours.

The pie chart illustrates the distribution of digital revenue among different segments of U.S. publishers in 2012. The Business-to-business segment accounts for 35% of the revenue, Consumer for 30%, Average for 25%, and Association for 10%. Each slice represents the percentage share of each segment's contribution to the total digital revenue.

The pie chart illustrates the market share of three largest U.S. broadband providers over a span from 2006 to 2013. In 2006, provider A holds 45%, B has 30%, and C accounts for 25%. The line chart illustrates the unemployment rate in Greece from 1999 to 2020. The data points show fluctuations over the years, starting at 12% in 1999 and ending at 17% in 2020. A dip occurs in 1999 at 1.2 billion, followed by a gradual rise to 11.4 billion in 2020. Projections for future years indicate a continued growth trend, reaching 18.1 billion by 2026.

The pie chart illustrates the projected share of Moldova's global GDP adjusted for Purchasing Power Parity (PPP) from 2016 to 2026. Each year is represented as an equal slice, indicating that Moldova's share is expected to remain constant at 9.1% over the decade. The years 2017 through 2026 are marked with an asterisk, suggesting they are future projections.

The line chart illustrates the inflation rate in Moldova from 1996 to 2026*. The data shows fluctuations over the years, with the highest inflation rate recorded in 1999 at 39.2% and the lowest in 2009 at 0.2%. Other notable peaks include 1996 at 23.5%, 2000 at 31.4%, and 2008 at 12.7%. The chart also includes projections for future years, with predicted rates ranging from 5.2% in 2021 to 5.6% in 2026.

The line chart illustrates the share of drivers in the United Kingdom who consider the price of petrol or diesel as one of their greatest concerns, spanning from 2013 to 2018. The concern level dropped further to 24% in 2016 before rising to 28% in 2017 and 29% in 2018.

The histogram illustrates the reasons why motorists in the United Kingdom (UK) did not use public transport in 2018. Environmental issues garner 17 votes, while foreign affairs and defense are at 13 and 12 votes. Issues related to crime, corruption, and the judiciary receive fewer votes, ranging from 8 to 6 votes. The least voted topic is the right to abortion, with 2 votes.

The histogram illustrates the number of facilities where cluster coronavirus (COVID-19) infections emerged in South Korea as of March 11, 2020, categorized by type. Medical facilities lead with 20 cases, followed by social welfare facilities at 8, religious facilities at 7, work-related facilities at 6, and multi-use facilities at 4.

The histogram illustrates the need for closing oncology and specialist hospitals in Poland due to COVID-19 in 2020. It shows three categories: 'Yes' with a value of 36, indicating some facilities were closed; 'No' with a value of 61, suggesting most facilities did not close; and 'Other' with a value of 3, representing an unspecified category.

The line chart illustrates the number of tourist arrivals in Iceland's accommodation from 2009 to 2019. In 2009, there were 1,800,000 arrivals, which increased to 2,200,000 by 2012. The trend shows a steady rise with 3,400,000 arrivals in 2015, peaking at 5,500,000 in 2018 before slightly decreasing to 5,400,000 in 2019. Each year marks a growth in the number of tourists staying in Icelandic accommodations.

The bar chart illustrates attempts to limit statements about the operation of oncological hospitals during the COVID-19 pandemic in Poland in 2020. There were 40 instances where such limitations were attempted, and 60 instances where they were not.

The histogram illustrates the number of flu-related deaths in the U.S. during the 2019-2020 flu season, categorized by age group. The data shows that all ages combined had 20,546 deaths, with the highest number occurring among those aged 65+ at 11,783. Younger groups had fewer deaths: 342 for ages 0-4 years and 189 for ages 5-17 years. The 18-49 year-olds had 2,187 deaths, while those aged 50-64 years experienced 6,082 deaths.

The line chart illustrates Kansas's annual per capita personal consumption expenditures (PCE) from 2000 to 2020, measured in U.S. dollars. Starting at $25,000 in 2000, there is an upward trend with fluctuations over the years. By 2004, PCE increased to $24,000, and by 2008 it reached $30,000. A dip occurred in 2009 to $26,000 before rising to $31,000 in 2010. The subsequent years show a general increase, with peaks at $39,000 in 2019 and $38,000 in 2020. The data points for each year are plotted on the chart.

The line chart illustrates the annual volume of gas vented during offshore oil production in the United Kingdom from 2006 to 2019, measured in metric tons. The data shows fluctuations over the years, starting at 25,000 metric tons in 2006 and reaching its highest point of 95,000 metric tons in 2019. Other years display varying volumes, such as 33,000 metric tons in 2008, 42,000 metric tons in 2010, and 45,000 metric tons in 2011. The trend appears to be generally upward with some dips, like in 2014 when it dropped to 37,000 metric tons.

The bar chart illustrates Russians' intentions to participate in the constitutional voting in 2020, measured over five dates. On February 20th, 23% had not decided yet, while 41% said 'Yes, I will', and 25% preferred 'Rather yes'. By March 11th, undecided decreased to 20%, with 'Yes, I will' rising to 45%. April 17th saw a slight decrease in undecided to 19%, but 'Yes, I will' increased to 47%. In May, undecided was at 19%, with 'Yes, I will' at 46%. On June 22nd, undecided dropped to 13%, with 'Yes, I will' reaching its peak at 54%.

The line chart illustrates the recorded music revenue in Denmark from 2015 to 2019, measured in million Danish Krone (DKK). In 2015, the revenue was 450 million DKK, which increased steadily each year, reaching 610 million DKK by 2019. The data points show a consistent growth trend over the five-year period.

The bar chart illustrates the changes in animal product consumption among French households in 2019, categorized by type of product. It shows that 72% reduced or stopped consuming red meat, while 28% increased or maintained their consumption. For milk, 39% decreased or halted consumption, and 61% continued to consume it at the same level. Cheese saw a 29% reduction or cessation, with 71% maintaining or increasing their intake. Yogurt had the highest percentage of those who increased or maintained their consumption at 76%, with only 24% reducing or stopping its consumption.

The histogram illustrates the results of a survey conducted at an oncological center in Poland during 2020, focusing on patient health analysis and epidemiological interviews. It shows that 89 patients had their visit to the hospital preceded by an analysis of their condition and an epidemiological interview (temperature measurement, conversation, or previous exposure survey). In contrast, 12 patients did not have such a preceding process, and 4 patients were unsure if they had undergone this procedure before visiting the hospital.

The line chart illustrates the Consumer Price Index (CPI) projections for Vietnam in 2020, considering two scenarios regarding the end of the COVID-19 outbreak. Scenario 1 assumes the pandemic ends in Q1 2020, with CPI rising from 4.0 in January to 4.5 by December. Scenario 2 projects the outbreak ending in Q2 2020, leading to a CPI increase from 4.0 in January to 4.3 by December. The chart shows monthly CPI values for both scenarios, highlighting the potential impact on inflation over the year.

The bar chart illustrates attitudes towards paid and ad-supported podcasts in the U.S. in 2020, segmented by ethnicity. Hispanics are evenly split between the two options (38% each), whereas Other ethnicities favor all podcasts costing money and being ad-free (12%).

The histogram illustrates the ranking of average daily distances traveled by public transport users in various cities within France for the year 2019. Lyon's average is 4.7 kilometers, Nantes & Saint-Nazaire at 4.7 kilometers as well, and Strasbourg has the lowest average at 3.9 kilometers.

The candlestick chart illustrates the impact of COVID-19 on global internet performance in 2020, showing changes in fixed and mobile internet speeds for various countries. Other countries like Germany, France, China, Japan, and India also show varying degrees of change in their internet speeds during this period. The data reflects the diverse effects of the pandemic on internet connectivity across different nations.

The line chart illustrates Vermont's annual per capita personal consumption expenditures (PCE) from 2000 to 2020, measured in U.S. dollars. The bar chart illustrates the number of deaths in the U.S. caused by heat, categorized by age group from 2004 to 2018. For instance, there were 160 deaths with heat-related codes as an underlying cause for individuals under one year old, compared to 900 deaths where heat was a contributing factor. The highest numbers are seen in the 45-54 age group, with 1100 deaths due to heat as an underlying cause and 680 as a contributing cause.

The bar chart illustrates the number of deaths in the U.S. caused by heat, categorized by gender and age group from 2004 to 2018. It shows that males generally outnumber females in heat-related fatalities across all age groups. For instance, there were 120 male and 50 female deaths in the <1 year old category, while the 85+ age group had 420 male and 520 female deaths. The highest number of deaths occurred among those aged 55-64, with 1400 males and 500 females affected.

The bar chart illustrates Hawaii's electoral votes in U.S. presidential elections from 1960 to 2020. It shows the number of electoral votes each party received, as well as any faithless electors. The pattern continues with varying numbers for subsequent elections, such as Richard Nixon receiving 4 Democratic and 6 Republican votes in 1972, and Barack Obama winning all 4 Democratic votes in 2008. In 2020, Joe Biden secured all 4 Democratic votes, while Donald Trump received 3 Republican votes, with one faithless elector casting their vote for Joe Biden.

The chart visually segments these percentages to show the proportion of online music listeners between the two regions.

The bar chart illustrates the prevalence of arthritis among U.S. adults in 2020, segmented by gender and state. It shows the percentage of males and females with arthritis across various states, including California, Texas, New York, Florida, and others. For example, California has 35% of its male population and 42% of its female population affected by arthritis. The data extends to Puerto Rico, which reports 18% for males and 45% for females. Each state's figures are presented as individual bars, allowing for a visual comparison between genders within each state.

The line chart illustrates the number of automated meter readers installed in the United States from 2008 to 2020, measured in millions. The data points show fluctuations over the years: starting at 45.6 million in 2008, peaking at 48.7 million in 2010 and 2012, with a dip to 37.2 million by 2020. The trend indicates an initial increase followed by a decline, with the highest installation numbers occurring in the early years of the period shown.

The histogram illustrates the purchasing locations for detox drinks among French consumers in 2019. It shows that retail stores were the most popular with 65 purchases, followed by homemade options at 29. Organic stores accounted for 23 purchases, while specialized stores had 12. The pie chart illustrates the distribution of opinions on various actions against coronavirus in Poland for 2020. It shows that 28% of people support quarantine for individuals entering Poland from abroad, 27% prefer no visits to hospitals, 22% advocate for the prohibition of travel abroad, 15% favor the cancellation of classes at schools or universities, and 10% believe in the obligation to wear masks in public places.

The line chart illustrates the monthly average prices for old roumi cheese in Egypt from January 2019 to July 2020, measured in Egyptian pounds per kilogram. The data points show fluctuations over the period, with prices starting at $108 in January 2019 and reaching a peak of $109.5 in April 2020. There is a general trend of price increase until mid-2020, followed by a decline towards the end of the observed period.

The bar chart illustrates the percentage of U.S. adults who delayed or avoided medical care due to COVID-19 in June 2020, categorized by gender and type of care. Females accounted for 12% of those who delayed or avoided urgent or emergency care, compared to males at 13%. For routine care, females were 36%, while males were slightly higher at 27%. When it comes to any type of care, females delayed or avoided it 46% of the time, whereas males did so 36% of the time.

The bar chart illustrates the maturity of GovTech in Mexico for 2020 across various dimensions, each scored on an index. The procurement framework is rated at 8.3, startups' digital environment at 5.8, government's digital government at 5.7, and the average score is 5.2. Startups' innovation environment scores 4.6, while the government's policy environment is rated at 4.0. Procurement culture is given a score of 4.0, and startups' industry environment is also rated at 5.5.

The line chart illustrates the number of terrorist fatalities in the European Union and United Kingdom from 2010 to 2020. In 2010, there were 8 fatalities, which increased to 79 in 2011 before dropping to 16 in 2012. The number continued to fluctuate, reaching a peak of 150 fatalities in 2015, followed by a decrease to 143 in 2016. There was a notable drop to 12 fatalities in 2017, with subsequent increases to 13 in 2018 and 11 in 2019, ending with 25 fatalities in 2020.

The line chart illustrates the number of reported and charged crimes in Denmark from 2010 to 2020. In 2010, there were 550,000 reports with 120,000 charges. The following years show fluctuations; for instance, in 2011, reports decreased to 580,000 while charges rose to 140,000. By 2020, reports had dropped to 445,000, whereas charges increased to 170,000. Each year marks a different pattern in crime reporting and charging trends.

The line chart illustrates the number of reported and charged robberies in shops in Denmark from 2010 to 2020. In 2010, there were 850 reports with 710 charges. The following years show fluctuations; for instance, in 2012, there were 690 reports and 650 charges. The data peaks again in 2013 with 780 reports and 700 charges. By 2020, reports decreased to 320 while charges rose to 370. Each year marks a unique pattern in the reported versus charged cases of shop robberies.

The histogram illustrates the popularity of various search terms related to Donald Trump in the United States between September 2019 and August 2020. The term "trump" leads with a value of 10.4, followed by "donald trump" at 9.3, and "trump 2020" at 3.2. Other terms include "trump rally" (2.7), "trump rally schedule" (1.6), "trump store" (1.7), "trump campaign" (1.4), "trump merch" (1.3), "trump website" (1.2), and "maga hat" (1.0).

The line chart illustrates the trend in Medicare inpatient per-user actual costs from 2009 to 2019, measured in U.S. dollars. Starting at $16,500 in 2009, the cost gradually increases each year, reaching $23,000 by 2019. The data points for subsequent years show a consistent rise: $17,000 in 2010, $17,500 in 2011, $18,000 in 2012, and so on, with each year showing an increment of $500 over the previous year's cost.

The histogram illustrates the preferences for Christmas gifts in Mexico during 2020, showing the number of people who preferred different types of presents. Clothing and shoes were the most popular choice with 73% preference, followed by toys at 46%. Beauty products were favored by 37%, electronics by 28%, food and beverages by 23%, video games by 22%, home appliances by 20%, and jewelry by 15%.

The pie chart illustrates the distribution of funding for mental health as part of COVID-19 response efforts in August 2020. It shows that 73% of countries have partially allocated their funding to mental health and psychosocial support (MHPSS), while 27% have fully allocated their funding towards MHPSS.

The histogram illustrates the number of novel coronavirus (COVID-19) cases in various countries within the Asia-Pacific region as of January 19, 2022. India leads with 37,800,000 cases, followed by Indonesia at 4,050,000 and the Philippines at 3,200,000. Other countries with notable cases include the United States with 2,200,000, Thailand with 2,100,000, and Vietnam with 2,000,000. The data also includes figures for Australia, Japan, Bangladesh, Pakistan, Nepal, South Korea, Malaysia, Mongolia, Singapore, Laos, Cambodia, China, Fiji, Papua New Guinea, and others, with the lowest numbers reported for Macao and Bhutan.

The histogram illustrates daily installs of the most popular home screen customization app on the App Store over several dates in September 2020. The data points show that on 9/17/20, there were 0.1 million installs, which increased to 0.9 million on 9/18/20 and continued to rise, peaking at 3.1 million installs on 9/21/20. Installations then decreased slightly to 2.4 million on 9/22/20 before rising again to 2.5 million on 9/23/20.

The pie chart illustrates the distribution of businesses using e-commerce in Honduras by size in 2020. Large businesses account for 41% of e-commerce usage, medium-sized businesses make up 39%, and micro and small businesses represent 18%.

The bar chart illustrates the number of pupils in pre-primary school in Algeria from 2015 to 2020, categorized by gender. In the academic year 2015/2016, there were 227,000 females and 238,000 males. The following years show an increase with 245,000 females and 259,000 males in 2016/2017, 252,000 females and 267,000 males in 2017/2018, a slight decrease to 243,000 females and 256,000 males in 2018/2019, and a rise back to 249,000 females and 265,000 males in 2019/2020.

The pie chart illustrates the percentage of Medicare inpatient actual costs as a share of total costs from 2009 to 2019. In 2009, inpatient costs were 25% of total costs, decreasing slightly to 24% in 2010 and then fluctuating between 23% and 26% over the following years. The lowest percentage was observed in 2018 at 22%, while the highest was in 2009 at 27%. Each year is represented as a slice of the pie chart, showing the proportionate cost distribution for that year.

The bar chart illustrates slave exports from the Thirteen Colonies, categorized by origin (West Indies and Continental colonies) over five years from 1768 to 1772. In 1768, there were 109 slaves exported from the West Indies and 175 from Continental colonies. The following year saw a decrease in both categories with 10 slaves from the West Indies and 328 from Continental colonies. The trend continued downward in 1770 with 30 West Indies exports and 329 Continental ones. In 1771, there was only one export from the West Indies and 340 from Continental colonies. The year 1772 marked the lowest numbers, with just 3 West Indies exports and 490 from Continental colonies.

The bar chart illustrates dietary supplement usage among U.S. adults in 2020, categorized by household income brackets. Individuals with an income under $50K have a 68% usage rate, those earning between $50-100K show a 74% usage rate, and those with an income over $100K have the highest usage at 77%.

The histogram illustrates the top reasons for dietary supplement use among U.S. adults in 2019. The reasons are presented as percentages: "Overall health/wellness benefits" at 30%, "Energy" at 24%, "Immune health" at 20%, "Fill nutrient gaps" at 19%, "Healthy aging" at 18%, and "Heart health" also at 18%.

The bar chart illustrates the global reach rate of brand Instagram stories in 2018 and 2019, categorized by account size. Accounts with fewer than 10k followers had a reach rate of 12% in 2018 and 8.5% in 2019. Those with 10k to 50k followers saw a reach rate of 6% in 2018 and 5.5% in 2019. Accounts with 50k to 200k followers had a reach rate of 6% in both years, while those with over 200k followers had a reach rate of 4.3% in 2018 and 2.4% in 2019.

The histogram illustrates the top dietary supplement usage growth due to COVID-19 among U.S. adults in 2020. Multivitamins lead with an increase of 59%, followed by Vitamin C at 44%, and Vitamin D at 37%. Zinc shows a 17% increase, while Calcium has seen a 16% rise in usage during this period.

The histogram illustrates the bounce rate on websites of various cosmetic companies in France for the year 2020. Yves-Rocher.fr shows a bounce rate of 36%, while Feelunique.com has a slightly higher rate at 40%. KikoCosmetics.om's website has a 44% bounce rate, Loccitane.com at 48%, and Nocibe.fr at 48%. Sephora.fr and Marionnaud.fr both have a 50% bounce rate, whereas Beautysucces.fr and Notino.fr have rates of 52% and 58%, respectively. L'oreal-Paris.fr leads with the highest bounce rate at 61%.

The histogram illustrates the weekly development of the S&P 500 index from January 2020 to January 2022. Each bar represents a week, with the height corresponding to the index value in that week. The data spans from a low of 2450 on February 13, 2020, to a high of 4860 on December 27, 2021. The histogram illustrates various external challenges faced during remote working in Poland in 2020 due to the COVID-19 pandemic. The challenges include the possibility of making new contacts (30%), technical problems with equipment (28%), access to physical objects such as samples or products (13%), communication issues with customers or contractors (13%), misunderstandings due to poor communication (10%), and difficulties in accessing tools from customers or contractors (6%).

The line chart illustrates the number of female and male students enrolled in tertiary education in Tunisia from 2014 to 2019. In 2014, there were 210,000 females and 128,000 males. The following years show a decline for both genders: 2015 with 197,000 females and 123,000 males; 2016 with 184,000 females and 111,000 males; 2017 with 178,000 females and 105,000 males; 2018 with 173,000 females and 100,000 males; and 2019 with 171,000 females and 97,000 males.

The bar chart illustrates the number of victims of various criminal offenses in Norway from 2009 to 2019. Public order and integrity violations have 6,210 victims, traffic offenses 6,050, sexual offenses 4,987, and drug and alcohol offenses at the lower end with 1,985 victims.

The bar chart illustrates the impact of COVID-19 on tech companies' revenue and expenses worldwide in 2020, categorized by changes in financial status. It shows five categories: 'Large reduction', 'Reduction', 'Stayed the same', 'Increase', and 'Large increase'. For each category, two bars represent revenue and expenses as percentages. 'Large reduction' indicates a 33% decrease in revenue and a 15% decrease in expenses. 'Reduction' shows a 28% decrease in revenue and a 39% decrease in expenses. 'Stayed the same' reflects no change in both revenue and expenses at 25%. 'Increase' depicts an 8% rise in revenue and a 10% increase in expenses. Lastly, 'Large increase' shows a 6% increase in revenue and an 8% increase in expenses.

The bar chart illustrates the growth in the number of medical apps downloaded during the peak of the COVID-19 crisis in 2020, measured in millions, across various countries and globally. South Korea leads with a 135% increase, followed by India at 90%, and worldwide at 65%. Spain and the United Kingdom show a 65% and 60% increase respectively. Japan's figure stands at 55%, Italy at 40%, France at 35%, the United States at 30%, Germany at 30%, and China at 25%.

The line chart illustrates the number of police violence complaints in Brazil from 2011 to 2019. The data shows an upward trend with complaints increasing from 450 in 2011 to 1650 in 2018, followed by a slight decrease to 1480 in 2019. Each year is marked on the x-axis, and the corresponding number of complaints is plotted on the y-axis.

The histogram illustrates the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on tech employees' productivity levels when working from home in 2020. It shows three categories: 'More productive', 'About the same', and 'Less productive'. The 'More productive' category has a value of 58, indicating that it is the most common response. 'About the same' follows with a value of 24, while 'Less productive' has the lowest value at 17.

The histogram illustrates the number of police officers killed in Brazil during 2020, categorized by state. São Paulo leads with 49 deaths, followed by Rio de Janeiro with 44. Other states with notable numbers include Pernambuco (14), Minas Gerais (13), and Pará (13). The data also shows that Bahia had 11 deaths, while Piauí, Santa Catarina, and Amazonas each had 7. Maranhão, Mato Grosso do Sul, and Goiás recorded 5 deaths each. Ceará, Paraíba, and Pernambuco had 4 deaths, and Para Grande do Norte, Sergipe, Alagoas, Distrito Federal, Espírito Santo, Mato Grosso, and Amapá had fewer, with 3 to 1 death respectively.

The bar chart illustrates the compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of vertical farming worldwide between 2020 and 2027 for select countries. The United States shows a CAGR of 24.8%, China at 24.5%, Canada with 18.1%, Germany at 17.0%, and Japan has the lowest at 15.3%.

The line chart illustrates the average monthly prices for round rebar iron in Egypt from January 2019 to August 2020, measured in Egyptian pounds per metric ton. The data points show fluctuations over the period, starting at $12,000 in January 2019 and peaking at $13,500 in July 2019. There is a noticeable dip in prices after July 2019, with the lowest point reaching $10,000 in August 2020. The chart captures the volatility of the rebar iron market price within this timeframe.

The histogram illustrates the impact of canceling live sports due to the COVID-19 pandemic on daily life, as perceived by respondents in March 2020. It shows five categories: 'Strongly agree' with a value of 13, 'Somewhat agree' at 15, 'Somewhat disagree' with a value of 14, 'Strongly disagree' at 45, and 'Don't know/no opinion' also at 15.

The line chart illustrates North American sugar output by country from 1885 to 1988, with data on tons of sugar produced from cane and beets. Canada's production starts at 0.2 tons in 1885 and increases steadily to 2.3 tons by 1988. Mexico's production begins at 1.5 tons in 1885, rising to 2.7 tons by 1988. The USA's sugar from cane production shows fluctuations, starting at 2.5 tons in 1885 and reaching its peak at 4.6 tons in 1988. Sugar from beets in the USA also increases over time, beginning at 0.2 tons in 1885 and growing to 3.5 tons by 1988.

The bar chart illustrates the unit cost of recycling in Japan for various packaging types in 2022, measured in Japanese yen per kilogram. Plastic packaging has the highest cost at 51.3 yen, followed by glass bottles with other colors at 17.6 yen. Paper packaging costs 16.2 yen, while amber glass bottles are priced at 6.1 yen. Colorless glass bottles have a lower cost of 4.6 yen, and PET bottles are the least expensive at 4.4 yen per kilogram.

The histogram illustrates the number of people in prison in Norway in 2018, categorized by type of crime. The data shows that 1134 individuals were imprisoned for violence and maltreatment, while 1092 were convicted of drug-related offenses. Sexual offenses accounted for 597 cases, with other offenses for profit leading to 336 imprisonments. Property crimes resulted in 308 convictions, public order and integrity violations in 217 cases, and intentional damage in 49 cases. Traffic offenses led to 37 imprisonments, with other offenses causing 1 case each. Unknown group of offense had 67 cases, and there was no recorded imprisonment for murder.

The line chart illustrates the monthly average prices for beech, Sweden, and blank wood in Egypt during 2019-2020. Prices for beech wood fluctuate between $8500 and $9000, with a peak in May 2020 at $9000. Sweden wood's prices range from $5100 to $5700, peaking in February 2019 at $5700. Blank wood shows a consistent price of $4000 throughout the period, with no variation observed. The data spans from January 2019 to August 2020.

The histogram illustrates public opinion on tightening abortion rules in Poland for 2020. It shows four categories of responses: "Abortion should be legal in certain cases" with 62% support, "Abortion should be available on request, until the 12th week of pregnancy" with 22%, "Abortion should be prohibited" with 11%, and "I don't know" with 5%.

The histogram illustrates the distribution of Culture Recovery Fund (CRF) grants awarded to arts and culture organizations in England during 2020, categorized by funding round and grant value. Round one saw grants under one million GBP totaling 261.5 million GBP, while those over one million GBP amounted to 76.3 million GBP. In round two, grants under one million GBP were 78.4 million GBP, with over one million GBP grants at 19.7 million GBP.

The histogram illustrates unit sales in millions for various seafood varieties within the U.S. seafood department in 2019. Crab sales stand at 120 million, while other fin fish and anchovy/sardine both reach 100 million units. Tilapia, catfish, cod/scrod, clams, oysters, lobsters, and scallops have lower sales figures, ranging from 50 to 30 million units.

The line chart illustrates the monthly value of exports from Egypt in 2019-2020, segmented into non-petroleum exports, crude oil, petroleum products, and total exports. The line chart illustrates monthly sales of packaged units of medical cannabis extracts in Canada from October 2019 to March 2021. Sales figures fluctuate over the period, starting at 175,000 units in October 2019 and reaching a peak of 278,000 units in July 2020. There is a noticeable increase in sales from February 2020 onwards, with the highest point occurring in July 2020, followed by a slight decrease in August before rising again towards the end of the observed timeframe.

The histogram illustrates the percentage of Canadian patients who reported using medical cannabis for various conditions in 2020. Anxiety disorders were managed by 45% of patients, while depression was addressed by 39%. Insomnia affected 37% of users, and arthritis by 25%. A smaller portion used cannabis for other mental health conditions at 15%, and PTSD was managed by 15% of patients as well.

The bar chart illustrates the number of new coronavirus (COVID-19) cases in Czechia by age group and gender from 2020 to 2022. It shows data for women, men, and their totals across different age brackets: 0-14 years with 200,000 women, 150,000 men, and a total of 350,000; 15-24 years with 150,000 women, 120,000 men, totaling 270,000; 25-34 years with 180,000 women, 160,000 men, totaling 340,000; 35-44 years with 250,000 women, 220,000 men, totaling 470,000; 45-54 years with 230,000 women, 210,000 men, totaling 440,000; 55-64 years with 160,000 women, 140,000 men, totaling 300,000; 65-74 years with 120,000 women, 100,000 men, totaling 220,000; 75-84 years with 60,000 women, 40,000 men, totaling 100,000; and 85+ years with 30,000 women, 20,000 men, totaling 50,000.

The bar chart illustrates the reduction of various medications due to medical cannabis among Canadian patients in 2020, categorized by whether they had a medical document or not. Anti-inflammatory use decreased by 41% with and 42% without a medical document. Opioid pain relievers saw a 33% reduction for those with documents versus 18% without. Non-opioid pain relievers reduced by 32% with and 27% without documentation. Anti-depressants showed a 27% decrease with a medical document compared to 22% without. Sedatives/tranquilizers had a 22% reduction with documents and 18% without. Other medications experienced a 3% reduction with a document and 4% without. Lastly, there was no reduction in other medications for those with a medical document but a 32% reduction for those without.

The bar chart illustrates the impact of COVID-19 on medical cannabis purchasing among Canadian patients in 2020, categorized by whether they have a medical document or not. For those with a medical document, it took longer to access cannabis (28%) and was harder to access (19%), while for those without, it was more expensive to access (9%). Both groups reported no impact at all (47% and 68%, respectively). Additionally, 12% of those with a medical document changed where they purchase, compared to 8% without one. A smaller percentage indicated some other impact, with 5% versus 4% respectively.

The line chart illustrates the use of fertilizers for agriculture in Algeria from 2015 to 2019, measured by the amount of nitrogen (N), phosphate (P2O5), and potash (K2O) used each year. In 2015, nitrogen usage was at 8.8 million tons, phosphate at 7.5 million tons, and potash at 4.5 million tons. By 2019, nitrogen decreased to 8.3 million tons, phosphate to 6.9 million tons, and potash to 3.1 million tons. The data shows a general downward trend in the use of these three nutrients over the five-year period.

The line chart illustrates monthly export values from Suez Port in Egypt for 2019-2020, alongside total port exports. In January 2019, Suez Port's exports were $250K with total port exports at $2.3M. The chart captures fluctuations over these months, with both the Dekheila Port and total export values showing peaks and troughs throughout the period.

The histogram illustrates the main concerns of Polish society during the COVID-19 pandemic in 2020. It shows that 82% worried about the economy, 75% about citizens' freedom, 74% about the permanent closure of the country due to the virus, and 71% about the further worsening of the situation. Concerns also included government's inability to protect the population (67%), the environment (53%), social distancing (53%), and the lack of vaccine availability (50%). A smaller percentage was worried about the spread of misinformation (47%) and other worries throughout the crisis (47%).

The histogram presents the results of a poll on whether each citizen, including those in work, should receive a guaranteed income from the state without work requirement in 2019. The responses are categorized into three groups: 'Strongly agree or rather agree' at 36%, 'Strongly disagree or rather disagree' at 42%, and 'Don't know or neither agree or disagree' at 22%.

The line chart illustrates the production of glass fiber reinforced plastics (GRP) in Spain and Portugal from 2012 to 2020, measured in thousands of metric tons. The data shows fluctuations over the years, with an initial increase from 160,000 metric tons in 2012 to 167,000 metric tons in 2018. A slight decrease is observed in 2019 at 166,000 metric tons, followed by a sharp decline to 141,000 metric tons in 2020.

The bar chart illustrates the main concerns of Poles about material goods in Poland for 2020. It shows two categories: "Breaking into bank account" with a value of 69, and "Home break-in" with a value of 56. The chart likely represents the frequency or impact of these concerns among Polish individuals.

The histogram illustrates the types of second-hand items bought by French individuals in the clothing, textile, and footwear categories for 2018. Home textiles were purchased by 26% of respondents, while accessories and leather goods were chosen by 1% each. The 'Others' category accounted for 1% of purchases as well.

The bar chart illustrates the growth in CDA's stock exchange rate due to the COVID-19 pandemic in Poland during 2020. On March 12, the growth was recorded at 39%, while on March 13, it decreased to 13%. The following day, on March 14, there was an increase to 50% growth.

The line chart illustrates Barrick Gold's market capitalization over time, measured in billion Canadian dollars, from April 2019 to October 2020. The bar chart illustrates the percentage share of child slaves along select routes from 1636 to 1867, categorized by different nationalities. Each nationality's route displays a unique pattern of change over time.

The histogram illustrates the religious involvement of individuals in Poland during the COVID-19 pandemic in 2020. It shows the percentage of people who reported their religious commitment as the same, increased, decreased, or not sure compared to before the pandemic. 61% said their commitment remained the same, 22% reported an increase, 11% noted a decrease, and 4% were unsure about changes in their religious commitment.

The line chart illustrates the annual value of natural rubber exports from Singapore between 2016 and 2020, measured in million U.S. dollars. In 2016, the export value was $95 million, which increased to $118 million by 2017. The following year saw a slight decrease to $108 million, then a further drop to $98 million in 2019. The trend continued downward in 2020, with the export value reaching its lowest point at $90 million.

The histogram illustrates the distribution of Romanians' preferences for working from home in 2020, categorized by the number of days they would like to work from home per week. The data shows that 12 individuals prefer 5 days at home and 0 in the office, while 16 people prefer 4 days at home and 1 day in the office. Preferences continue with 18 people choosing 2 days at home and 3 days in the office, 15 preferring 1 day at home and 4 days in the office, and 7 opting for no days at home and 5 days in the office. Additionally, there are smaller groups with 2 weeks in the office and 2 at home, or 1 week each, and one individual prefers alternating weeks between the office and home.

The bar chart illustrates the opinions of French parents regarding their daughters having "boy" toys in 2019. It shows two scenarios: when the daughter already has "boy" toys, with 70% of parents saying yes and 30% saying no; and when parents intend to buy their daughters "boy" toys, with 60% of parents agreeing and 40% disagreeing.

The bar chart illustrates the prevalence of mental distress among U.S. adults with disabilities in 2018, segmented by gender. It shows that 28% of male adults and 37% of female adults experienced mental distress. The data suggests a higher incidence of mental distress among females compared to males within this demographic group.

The bar chart illustrates the share of U.S. physicians' levels of upset for various reasons during the COVID-19 pandemic in August 2020. Physicians expressed varying degrees of upset, with percentages ranging from 7% to 58%, indicating the extent of their dissatisfaction across these issues.

Other changes included practice closures (8% vs. 18%), new employment (6% vs. 9%), reduced patient care (5% vs. 3%), and an increase in locum tenens work (3% vs. 6%).

The bar chart illustrates the intention of people in Brazil to get vaccinated against COVID-19 as of May 2021. It shows four categories: 'Yes' with 67%, indicating those who planned to get vaccinated, 'Already vaccinated' at 25%, 'No' at 8%, and 'Did not know' at 1%.

The line chart illustrates Peru's trade values from 2015 to 2020, distinguishing between imports and exports in billions of dollars. In 2015, imports were at 38 billion with exports at 34 billion. In 2018, there was a notable rise with imports reaching 45 billion and exports peaking at 48 billion. The trend reversed in 2019, with imports at 42 billion and exports at 46 billion. Finally, in 2020, both imports and exports decreased to 36 billion each.

The histogram illustrates public opinion on the effectiveness of government actions regarding the COVID-19 pandemic in Poland for 2020. It shows five categories: 'Definitely yes' with 7.5%, 'Rather yes' with 35.2%, 'Rather no' with 28.4%, 'Definitely no' with 21.3%, and 'I don't know, hard to say' with 7.5%. The percentages represent the proportion of respondents who fall into each category.
